Class MoviePlayer

  • java.lang.Object
    • OOP_Project.Product
      • OOP_Project.MoviePlayer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Item, MultimediaControl

    public class MoviePlayer
extends Product
implements MultimediaControl
    The MoviePlayer class inherits Product and implements the methods from MultimediaControl who's body are filled in here. Then it declares two private variables screen and monitorType. Creates a constructor called MoviePlayer that accepts 4 parameters, calls its parents constructor and sets the ItemType to "VISUAL". After that we create a method called toString which returns the parents toString method + our local toString method that will print out our screen and monitor values.
